HB 992 Original 2026 Regular Session Freiberg
Abstract: Requires the assignment of student identification numbers to children in certain
early learning programs.
Present law provides for the collection and use of certain student data and information for
specified purposes.
Present law requires each local public school board to assign a student identification number
to every student enrolled in a public elementary or secondary school.
Proposed law retains present law.
Proposed law requires the state Dept. of Education (DOE) to assign such a number to every
child participating in a publicly funded program at one of the following:
(1) A prekindergarten program at a school.
